<bioghist id="bioghist">

<p>Mountain Day has remained a unique and much-anticipated holiday at Smith College since it was first celebrated in October 1877.  According to an article written in The Sophian in 1970, "On this occasion, the date of which is unknown to all except [the college president], bells ring to announce a surprise holiday on which all academic appointments are cancelled."  Students are encouraged to use this day to take long walks or bike rides and to enjoy a beautiful fall day free from the stress of everyday life.
</p>
</bioghist>
<scopecontent id="scope">

<p>The majority of the material is composed of photographs and newspaper clippings documenting Smith's celebration of Mountain Day from 1882 to the present.  All of the materials are arranged chronologically, while undated and miscellaneous materials are located at the back of each document box.
</p>
</scopecontent>
<arrangement id="scope-arr">

<p>The material is arranged chronologically.


</p>
</arrangement>
